      <title>Re: eZ Webin - doesn't work for me - Bug?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezstyleeditor/forum/general/ez_webin_doesn_t_work_for_me_bug/re_ez_webin_doesn_t_work_for_me_bug2</link>
      <description>hi,&#13;
&#13;
I had a similar problem. After moving &#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
ActiveExtensions[]=ezjscore&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
below &#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
ActiveExtensions[]=ezstyleeditor&#13;
ActiveExtensions[]=ezwebin&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
and doing&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
php bin/php/ezpgenerateautoloads.php -e -p&#13;
php bin/php/ezcache.php --clear-all --purge&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;&#13;
&#13;
it worked.&#13;
&#13;
best of luck&#13;
&#13;
sebastian</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Sebastian Schoeller)</author>
