    <item>
      <title>Installation</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/ezstyleeditor/forum/general/installation</link>
      <description>You might want to clarify in the installation instructions that to use the edit features you need the eZ Website Toolbar extension too... (unless there is some other way of using this without the toolbar?)  And, if you have the toolbar extension, make sure you add the:&#13;
&#13;
ActiveExtensions[]=ezstyleeditor&#13;
&#13;
line above the:&#13;
&#13;
ActiveExtensions[]=ezwt&#13;
&#13;
line in the site.ini &#13;
&#13;
Otherwise the css button never shows up.&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
&#13;
</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Steven E Bailey)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/ezstyleeditor/forum/general/installation</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 21 Jan 2010 13:15:32 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
